request.description:
Manage accounts entry point

authenticationOrder: 1: local first 2: ldap first RW Priority for authentication

Return admin account data

id: read-only integer >0, unique identifier within the account collection

credentials:

enabled: read/write boolean, indicates whether the account is active or not

username: read/write string 

password: write-only string 

passwordExpired: read/write boolean, written to true requires the user to change the password at the next connection 
 
accountPassword: write-only string, define the password from the user who want to edit this account

locked: read/write boolean, true if password is expired, written to false to unlock user

profile: read/write string, example 
    "/rest/mbdetnrs/1.0/accountsService/profiles/1"

realm: read/write integer
    0: unknown
    1: local
    2: ldap
    3: radius read-only realm of the user account 

predefined: read-only boolean, when true this account cannot be deactivated, account is not removable, roles are not modifiable

vCard:

fullName: read/write string

email: read/write string 

phone: read/write string 

organization: read/write string

preferences:

notifyByMail: read/write boolean 

licenseAgreed: read/write boolean, false by default 

language: read/write string, "en" by default

dateFormat: read/write string, "m/d/Y" by default

timeFormat: read/write integer
    0: 12 hour
    1: 24 hour

temperatureUnit: read/write integer
    0: Kelvin
    1: Celcius
    2: Fahrenheit

request.description:
Network card firmware upgrade action

Errors:

403: Current user has no enough privileges 

413: Request Entity Too Large 

423: An upgrade is already pending 

507: Insufficient storage

http.HTTP:
POST /rest/mbdetnrs/1.0/managers/1/actions/upgrade HTTP/1.1
Host: {{domain}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
Content-Length: 199
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="upgradeFile"; filename="file"
Content-Type: <Content-Type header here>

(data)
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

request.description:
Return firmware upgrade status

JSON:

{

"step": [0-7],

"flashProgress": [percentage complete],

"error": "[plain text error]"

}

step:

0: Not initiated (auto reset to after "done" for 10s )

1: Transferring

2: Verifying package

3: Flashing firmware (see flashProgress for a detail 
progression)

4: Configuring system

5: Flashing bootloader

6: Done (check error field to know if any error occured)

7: Rebooting (set 5 seconds before the card reboot to let the UI retrieve the reboot step before TNTNet is killed)

Return all firmware instances

JSON: { "members@count": 2, "members": [ { "id": 1, "@id": "/rest/mbdetnrs/1.0/managers/1/firmwares/1", "firmwareVersion": "02.04.1234", "firmwareDate": , "firmwareSha": "bbb1c64", "installationDate": , "status": [0-4], "activationDate": }, { "id": 2, "@id": "/rest/mbdetnrs/1.0/managers/1/firmwares/2", "firmwareVersion": "02.03.6789", "firmwareDate": , "firmwareSha": "abcd122", "installationDate": , "status": [0-4], "activationDate": } ] }

Fields definition

firmwareVersion: read-only string, firmware version

firmwareDate: read-only integer, UNIX timestamp of firmware release date

firmwareSha: read-only string, first 7 digits of firmware SHA1 in GIT repository

installationDate: read-only integer, UNIX timestamp set to current time by upgrade process once flashing is done and verified. Reset to 0 by upgrade process on partition erasure.

status: read-only integer, status of firmware image 0: uploading 1: invalid 2: valid 3: pending reboot 4: active 5: flashing

activationDate: read-only integer, UNIX timestamp set to current time at first boot (the first time firmware is activated). Reset to 0 by upgrade process on partition erasure.
